{
  "texts": [
    "Approximately 30 participants indicated that LLMs contributed 1-25% of content in some of their manuscripts.",
    "At the same time, 37 pathologists familiar with ChatGPT reported no usage of LLMs in their published works.",
    "In a subgroup of 24 participants who employed GPT-4 for programming-related tasks, LLMs were predominantly utilized for developing command-line programs and scripts, as reported by 20 users, followed by creating coding tutorials (14 users) and performing code clean-up (11 users).",
    "GPT-4 was deemed moderately reliable for these coding tasks, receiving an average reliability rating of 3.4 out of 5.",
    "In terms of efficiency, it was highly valued for its time-saving capabilities, with an average rating of 4.1 out of 5."
  ]
}